
⭐️

Character here is not a variable.
It is a built-in Java class from the package java.lang.
The Character class provides a set of static methods (utility methods) for working with characters, such as:
Character.isUpperCase(ch) → checks if a character is uppercase
Character.isLowerCase(ch) → checks if a character is lowercase
Character.isDigit(ch) → checks if a character is a digit
Character.toLowerCase(ch) → converts to lowercase
Character.toUpperCase(ch) → converts to uppercase ️
⭐️
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);
        String str = scanner.nextLine();

        for (int i = 0; i < str.length(); ) {
            if (Character.isUpperCase(str.charAt(i))) {
                System.out.print(str.charAt(i));
                i++;
                while (i < str.length() && !Character.isUpperCase(str.charAt(i))) {
                    System.out.print(str.charAt(i));
                    i++;
                }
                System.out.println();
            }
        }
        
    }
}

